*ACTIVATE_ELEMENTS
"Optional title"
coid,  entype,  enid,  t_birth,  t_death,  ξ
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
coid           : Command ID
entype         : Entity type
                 options: ALL, ES, G, GS, P, PS
enid           : Entity ID
t_birth        : Time or FUNCTION defining element activation
                 default: 0.0
t_death        : Time or FUNCTION defining element deactivation
                 default: 1.0e10
ξ              : Optional strength of not yet activated elements
                 default: 0
#example
    *ACTIVATE_ELEMENTS
    1, P, 3, fcn(1000), fcn(2000)
    *FUNCTION
    1000
    abs(xs(3)-xs(2))-%L
    *FUNCTION
    2000
    -(abs(xs(2)-xs(3))-%L)
#end

*ADD_MASS
"Optional title"
coid,  entype,  enid,  m_add,  distribution
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
coid           : Command ID
entype         : Entity type
                 options: N, G, P, PS
enid           : Entity ID
m_add          : Added mass or added mass per unit area (constant, CURVE or FUNCTION)
                 options: constant, fcn
distribution   : Mass distribution type
                 options:
                 0 -> node mass weighted distribution (m_add defines total mass)
                 1 -> area weighted distribution (m_add defines total mass)
                 2 -> area weighted distribution (m_add defines mass per unit area)
                 3 -> directional area weighted distribution (m_add defines mass per unit area)

*BALANCE_SURFACE_MASS
"Optional title"
coid
pid,  gid
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
coid           : Command ID (optional)
pid            : Part ID
gid            : Optional geometry ID

*BC_MOTION
"Optional title"
bcid
entype,  enid,  bc_tr,  bc_rot,  csysid_tr,  csysid_rot,  t_beg,  t_end
pmeth_1,  direc_1,  cid_1,  sf_1,  fid_1
.
pmeth_n,  direc_n,  cid_n,  sf_n,  fid_n
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
bcid           : Boundary conditions ID (optional)
entype         : Entity type
                 options: N, NS, P, PS, ALL, G, GS
enid           : Entity identification number
bc_tr          : Translational constraints
                 options: 0, X, Y, Z, XY, YZ, ZX, XYZ
bc_rot         : Rotational constraint
                 options: 0, X, Y, Z, XY, YZ, ZX, XYZ
csysid_tr      : Coordinate system ID for translational constraints
csysid_rot     : Coordinate system ID for rotational constraints (0 for rotation around COG)
t_beg          : Activation time
t_end          : Termination time
                 default: 1.0e10
pmeth_1        : Method used to prescribe motion (acceleration/velocity or displacement)
                 options:
                 A -> acceleration
                 V -> velocity
                 D -> displacement
direc_1        : Direction of prescribed motion
                 options: X, Y, Z, RX, RY, RZ
cid_1          : ID of a CURVE or FUNCTION defining prescribed motion
sf_1           : Scale factor for curve ordinate values
                 default: 1
fid_1          : ID of optional activation function
                 default: not used
pmeth_n        : Method used to prescribe motion (acceleration/velocity or displacement)
                 options:
                 A -> acceleration
                 V -> velocity
                 D -> displacement
direc_n        : Direction of prescribed motion
                 options: X, Y, Z, RX, RY, RZ
cid_n          : ID of a CURVE or FUNCTION defining prescribed motion
sf_n           : Scale factor for curve ordinate values
                 default: 1
#example
    *BC_MOTION
    2
    P, 2, XY, XYZ
    V, Z, 1000
    *CURVE
    1000
    0,     -1
    0.004, -1
    0.0051, 1
    1,      1
#end
   
*BC_PERIODIC
"Optional title"
bcid
entype_1,  enid_1,  entype_2,  enid_2
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
bcid           : Boundary conditions ID
entype_1       : Entity type of Surface 1
                 options: G, GS, NS, FS
enid_1         : Entity identification number of Surface 1
entype_2       : Entity type of Surface 2
                 options: G, GS, NS, FS
enid_2         : Entity identification number of Surface 2

*BC_SYMMETRY
plane,  csysid_1,  csysid_2,  csysid_3,  tol
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
plane          : Symmetry planes through the origin
                 options: 0, X, Y, Z, XY, YZ, ZX, XYZ
csysid_1       : ID of coordinate system defining location and orientation (optional) of first symmetry plane. This input is only active if plane=0.
csysid_2       : ID of coordinate system defining location and orientation (optional) of second symmetry plane. This input is only active if plane=0.
csysid_3       : ID of coordinate system defining location and orientation (optional) of third symmetry plane. This input is only active if plane=0.
tol            : maximum distance between a node and the symmetry plane for symmetry conditions to be applied (optional)

*BC_TELEPORT
"Optional title"
bcid
entype,  enid,  csysid,  trig,  multiple,  velocity
Δ_x,  Δ_y,  Δ_z,  θ_x,  θ_y,  θ_z,  Δv_x,  Δv_y,  Δv_z
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
bcid           : Boundary conditions ID (optional)
entype         : Entity type
                 options: P, PS
enid           : Entity identification number
csysid         : Optional coordinate system ID
                 default: global coordinates are used
trig           : Time or FUNCTION (fcn) to trigger teleportation
                 options: time or fcn
multiple       : Flag to allow for multiple teleportations
                 options:
                 0 -> maximum once
                 1 -> teleport every time the trig function returns a positive value
velocity       : Flag to keep velocities after teleportation
                 options:
                 0 -> reset velocities
                 1 -> keep velocities
Δ_x, Δ_y, Δ_z  : Teleportation displacement or FUNCTION (fcn)
                 options: scalar value or fcn
θ_x, θ_y, θ_z  : Teleportation rotation (rad) or FUNCTION (fcn)
                 options: scalar value or fcn
Δv_x, Δv_y, Δv_z: Teleportation velocity or FUNCTION (fcn)
                 options: scalar value or fcn

*BC_TEMPERATURE
"Optional title"
entype,  enid,  cid,  sf,  t_beg,  t_end
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
entype         : Entity type
                 options: G, P, PS;
enid           : Entity identification number
cid            : ID of a CURVE or FUNCTION defining temperature versus time
sf             : Temperature curve scale factor
                 default: 1
t_beg          : Start time
                 default: 0
t_end          : End time
                 default: 1.0e10

*BOLT_FAILURE
"Optional title"
coid
pid,  tabid,  T_fail,  S_fail,  W_fail
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
coid           : Command ID
pid            : Bolt part ID
tabid          : ID of table with bolt coordinates
T_fail         : Tensile failure force
                 default: no failure
S_fail         : Shear failure force
                 default: no failure
W_fail         : Minimum absorbed energy prior to failure

*CFD_BLAST_1D
"Optional title"
coid, Stype, sbdid_gas, sbdid_exp
m_exp, R_exp, R_max, R_term, n_cells, n_dump
t_det, R_det, r_thres, i_write, dt_cfl
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
coid           : Command ID                                                                                                                                                                                                                   
Stype          : Simulation type
                 options:
                 0 -> Spherical air blast (full radial symmetry)
                 1 -> Hemispherical air blast (half radial symmetry)
                 2 -> Pipe (no spherical damping)
                 default: 0 
sbdid_gas      : Subdomain ID for command *CFD_GAS                                                                                                                                 
sbdid_exp      : Subdomain ID for command *CFD_HE                                                                                                                                     
m_exp          : Explosive mass                                                                                                                                                                                                                
R_exp          : Inner radius of explosive (Outer radius determined by mass an inner radius)                                                                                                                                                   
R_max          : Outer radius of the domain (Inner radius R_min of the domain is 0)                                                                                                                                                            
R_term         : Blast wave termination radius (Terminate command when leading shock reaches this radius)                                                                                                                                      
n_cells        : Number of CFD cells within the computational domain                                                                                                                                                                           
n_dump         : Number of domain dumps to file during simulation                                                                                                                                                                              
t_det          : Time of detonation initiation                                                                                                                                                                                                 
R_det          : Radius of detonation initiation                                                                                                                                                                                               
r_thres        : Density threshold value for when to switch between IGE and JWL EOS                                                                                                                                                            
i_write        : Time step interval to write to 2D bineary plot file (0 = do not write, 1 = each time step, 2 = every second time step, etc.)                                                                                                  
dt_cfl         : Stabilization parameter applied on the time step size. Default value is 0.5                                                                                                                                                   
               
*CFD_DETONATION
"Optional title"
coid
x_d,  y_d,  z_d,  t_d,  R,  path,  pid
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
coid           : Command ID
x_d, y_d, z_d  : Detonation point or function (fcn)
t_d            : Detonation time or function (fcn)
R              : Detonation radius
                 default: not used
path           : Detonation path
                 options:
                 0 -> radial detonation path
                 1 -> detonation path that accounts for obsacles and geometrical features
pid            : Part ID (defining region in space where detonation will occur)
                 default: not used

*CFD_DOMAIN
"Optional title"
coid,  scheme
entype,  enid,  Δ,  air,  geo_update,  xsmooth,  blocking_update,  blocking_type
x_0,  y_0,  z_0,  x_1,  y_1,  z_1
bc_x0,  bc_y0,  bc_z0,  bc_x1,  bc_y1,  bc_z1
t_end
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
coid           : Command ID
scheme         : Advection scheme
                 options:
                 1 -> Mixed 1st and 2nd order
                 2 -> Full 2nd order
                 default: 1
entype         : Structure entity type for fluid structure interaction
                 options: P, PS, ALL
enid           : Structure entity ID
Δ              : Cell size
air            : Option to begin with an air filled domain (before adding other materials)
                 options:
                 0 -> domain is empty
                 1 -> domain is filled with air
geo_update     : Coupling geometry update interval (number of time steps)
                 default: no update (geometry is assumed to be fixed in space)
xsmooth        : Spatial pressure smoothing level
                 default: inactive
blocking_update: CFD cell blocking criterion in FE coupling
                 options:
                 0 -> gt 0 % overlap
                 1 -> 100 % overlap
                 2 -> gt 50 % overlap
x_0            : CFD domain minimum x-coordinate
y_0            : CFD domain minimum y-coordinate
z_0            : CFD domain minimum z-coordinate
x_1            : CFD domain maximum x-coordinate
y_1            : CFD domain maximum y-coordinate
z_1            : CFD domain maximum z-coordinate
bc_x0          : Boundary condition at x=x_0
                 options:
                 0 -> non-reflecting boundary
                 1 -> reflecting boundary
bc_y0          : Boundary condition at y=y_0
                 options:
                 0 -> non-reflecting boundary
                 1 -> reflecting boundary
bc_z0          : Boundary condition at z=z_0
                 options:
                 0 -> non-reflecting boundary
                 1 -> reflecting boundary
bc_x1          : Boundary condition at x=x_1
                 options:
                 0 -> non-reflecting boundary
                 1 -> reflecting boundary
bc_y1          : Boundary condition at y=y_1
                 options:
                 0 -> non-reflecting boundary
                 1 -> reflecting boundary
bc_z1          : Boundary condition at z=z_1
                 options:
                 0 -> non-reflecting boundary
                 1 -> reflecting boundary
t_end          : Deactivation time
                 default: no CFD deactivation time

*CFD_GAS
"Optional title"
sbdid
type,  gid
ρ,  γ,  e_0,  C_v,  b
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
sbdid          : Subdomain ID
type           : Gas type
                 options:
                 AIR -> air at 1atm and 293K
                 USER -> user defined
gid            : Geometry ID
ρ              : Density (this line is only used if type=USER)
γ              : Fraction between C_p and C_v
e_0            : Initial internal energy per unit volume
C_v            : Heat capacity (optional)
                 default: not used
b              : Nobel-Abel co-volume parameter

*CFD_HE
"Optional title"
sbdid
type,  gid,  follow
ρ,  A,  B,  R_1,  R_2,  ω,  e_0,  D
e_ab,  t_ab,  C_v
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
sbdid          : Subdomain ID
type           : High explosive type
                 options:
                 preset -> ANFO 
                           C4 
                           COMPA 
                           COMPB 
                           HMX 
                           LX-10-1 
                           LX-14-0 
                           M46 
                           MCX-6100 
                           NSP-711 
                           OCTOL 
                           PBXN-110 
                           PBXN-9010 
                           PETN 
                           TETRYL 
                           TNT
                 user -> user defined
                 mid -> material ID
gid            : Geometry ID
follow         : Force material in CFD cells to follow the motion of overlapping elements
                 options:
                 0 -> no
                 1 -> yes
ρ              : Density (this line is only used if type=USER)
A              : JWL coefficient
B              : JWL coefficient
R_1            : JWL coefficient
R_2            : JWL coefficient
ω              : JWL coefficient
e_0            : Internal energy per unit volume, released at detonation
D              : Detonation velocity
e_ab           : Afterburn energy per unit volume at detonation time (optional)
t_ab           : Afterburn time parameter, controlling energy release rate (optional)
C_v            : Heat capacity
                 default: 711.14 J/kg K

*CFD_SOURCE
"Optional title"
coid
x_c,  y_c,  z_c,  R,  C_v,  γ,  cid_m,  cid_E
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
coid           : Command ID
x_c, y_c, z_c  : Source center coordinate
R              : Radius of source
C_v            : Heat capacity
γ              : Heat capacity ratio (C_p/C_v)
cid_dot m      : ID of a CURVE defining mass flow rate versus time
cid_dot E      : ID of a CURVE defining energy rate versus time

*CFD_STATE
"Optional title"
coid
x_c,  y_c,  z_c,  R,  C_v,  γ,  cid_ρ,  cid_e
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
coid           : Command ID
x_c, y_c, z_c  : Center coordinate
R              : Radius
C_v            : Heat capacity
γ              : Heat capacity ratio (C_p/C_v)
cid_ρ          : ID of a CURVE defining density versus time
cid_e          : ID of a CURVE defining specific energy versus time

*CFD_STRUCTURE_INTERACTION
"Optional title"
coid,  output,  δ_off
entype,  enid,  itype,  C_1,  C_2
fid_themal
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
coid           : Command ID
output         : Output flag
                 options:
                 0 -> no output
                 1 -> output
δ_off          : Optional coupling surface offset
                 default: no offset
entype         : Entity type
                 options: P, PS, ALL
enid           : Entity identification number
itype          : Interaction type
                 options:
                 1 -> blocking (default)
                 2 -> porous
C_1            : Coupling parameter 1
C_2            : Coupling parameter 2
fid_themal     : ID of a FUNCTION defining gas cooling due to heat transfer

*CFD_WIND_TUNNEL
"Optional title"
fid_v,  fid_ρ,  fid_T,  C_v,  γ,  Pambient
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
fid_v          : FUNCTION defining the inlet air flow velocity
fid_ρ          : FUNCTION defining the inlet air density
                 default: 1.2kg / m^3
fid_T          : FUNCTION defining the inlet air temperature
                 default: 293K
C_v            : Heat capacity
                 default: 711J / kgK
γ              : Heat capacity ratio (C_p / C_v)
Pambient       : Ambient pressure
                 options:
                 0 -> 1 atm
                 1 -> use inlet pressure

*CHANGE_P-ORDER
"Optional title"
entype,  enid,  order,  gid
------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
entype         : Entity type
                 options: P, PS, ALL
enid           : Entity identification number
order          : New element polynomial order
                 options: 1, 2, 3
gid            : ID of a GEOMETRY that defines a sub-space for change of polynomial order
                 default: No geometry. This means that all elements in the selected part/part set will change polynomial order

*CHANGE_PART_ID
"Optional title"
coid
pid_from,  pid_to,  gid
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
coid           : Command ID
pid_from       : Part ID before conversion
pid_to         : Part ID after conversion
gid            : Optional geometry ID

*COMPONENT_BOLT
"Optional title"
coid,  pid_1,  pid_2,  pid_3,  pid_4,  csysid,  tabid
D,  L,  h,  t
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
coid           : Component ID
pid_1          : Bolt part ID
                 default: no bolt
pid_2          : Nut part ID
                 default: no nut
pid_3          : Washer 1 part ID
                 default: no washer
pid_4          : Washer 2 part ID
                 default: no washer
csysid         : Local coordinate system ID
                 default: global coordinates are used
tabid          : Optional ID of TABLE with arbitrary number of bolt definitions
                 default: not used
D              : Bolt diameter
L              : Bolt length
h              : Axial distance between washers
t              : Washer thickness

*COMPONENT_BOX
"Optional title"
coid,  pid,  N_x,  N_y,  N_z,  csysid
x_1,  y_1,  z_1,  x_2,  y_2,  z_2
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
coid           : Component ID
pid            : Part ID
N_x            : Number of elements in local x-direction
N_y            : Number of elements in local y-direction
N_z            : Number of elements in local z-direction
csysid         : Local coordinate system ID. default: global coordinates are used
x_1, y_1, z_1  : Box corner coordinate 1
x_2, y_2, z_2  : Box corner coordinate 2

*COMPONENT_BOX_IRREGULAR
"Optional title"
coid,  pid,  N_1,  N_2,  N_3,  csysid
x_1,  y_1,  z_1,  x_2,  y_2,  z_2
x_3,  y_3,  z_3,  x_4,  y_4,  z_4
x_5,  y_5,  z_5,  x_6,  y_6,  z_6
x_7,  y_7,  z_7,  x_8,  y_8,  z_8
id1,  x_id1,  y_id1,  z_id1,  id2,  x_id2,  y_id2,  z_id2
.
idm,  x_idm,  y_idm,  z_idm,  idn,  x_idn,  y_idn,  z_idn
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
coid           : Component ID
pid            : Part ID
N_1            : Number of elements in 1-direction
N_2            : Number of elements in 2-direction
N_3            : Number of elements in 3-direction
csysid         : Local coordinate system ID
                 default: global coordinates are used
x_1, y_1, z_1, x_2, y_2, z_2: Box corner coordinates 1 and 2
x_3, y_3, z_3, x_4, y_4, z_4: Box corner coordinates 3 and 4
x_5, y_5, z_5, x_6, y_6, z_6: Box corner coordinates 5 and 6
x_7, y_7, z_7, x_8, y_8, z_8: Box corner coordinates 7 and 8
id1            : Optional mid-side edge coordinate ID
x_id1, y_id1, z_id1: Mid-side edge coordinate
id2            : Optional mid-side edge coordinate ID
x_id2, y_id2, z_id2: Mid-side edge coordinate
.              : 
idm            : Optional mid-side edge coordinate ID
x_idm, y_idm, z_idm: Mid-side edge coordinate
idn            : Optional mid-side edge coordinate ID
x_idn, y_idn, z_idn: Mid-side edge coordinate

*COMPONENT_CYLINDER
"Optional title"
coid,  pid,  N_1,  N_2,  csysid,  symmetry
x_1,  y_1,  z_1,  x_2,  y_2,  z_2,  R_1,  R_2
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
coid           : Component ID
pid            : Part ID
N_1            : Number of elements in axial direction
N_2            : Mesh density parameter
csysid         : Local coordinate system ID. Default: global coordinates are used
symmetry       : Optional command to define a half or quarter symmetry cylinder
                 options:
                 0: full model
                 1: half symmetry
                 2: quarter symmetry
x_1, y_1, z_1  : Face center coordinate 1
x_2, y_2, z_2  : Face center coordinate 2
R_1            : Radius at face 1
R_2            : Radius at face 2
                 Default:R1 = R2

*COMPONENT_PIPE
"Optional title"
coid,  pid,  N_1,  N_2,  N_3,  csysid,  α_c,  α_0
x_1,  y_1,  z_1,  x_2,  y_2,  z_2,  R_1,  R_2
R_3,  R_4
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
coid           : Component ID
pid            : Part ID
N_1            : Number of elements in axial direction
N_2            : Number of elements in circumferential direction
N_3            : Number of elements in thickness direction
csysid         : Local coordinate system ID.
                 default: global coordinates are used
α_c            : Angle in circumferential direction.
                 default: 360degree (full pipe)
α_0            : Start angle (only used if α_c < 360degree),
x_1, y_1, z_1  : Face center o_1 coordinate 1
x_2, y_2, z_2  : Face center o_2 coordinate 2
R_1            : First radius at o_1
R_2            : Second radius at o_2
R_3            : Inner radius at x2
                 default: R_3 = R_1
R_4            : Outer radius at x2
                 default: R_4 = R_2

