*CONNECTOR_SPOT_WELD
"Optional title"
coid
entype,  enid,  tabid,  tol
R,  h,  m,  k,  F_t,  F_s,  W_t,  W_s
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
coid           : Component ID
entype         : Entity type of sheets to be connected
                 options: P, PS, ALL
enid           : Entity ID of sheets to be connected
tabid          : Table ID of spot weld list
tol            : Maximum allowed distance between surfaces to be connected
R              : Spot weld radius
h              : Spot weld height
m              : Spot weld mass
k              : Spot weld stiffness
F_t            : Failure force - tear
F_s            : Failure force - shear
W_t            : Energy absorption - tear
W_s            : Enery absorption - shear

*CONNECTOR_SPOT_WELD_NODE
"Optional title"
coid,  nid,  pid,  N,  entype,  enid
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
coid           : Component ID
nid            : Node ID (node defining connector location)
pid            : Spot weld property command ID (PROP_SPOT_WELD)
N              : Number of connected plies
entype         : Entity type of sheets to be connected
                 options: P, PS
enid           : Entity ID of sheets to be connected

*CONNECTOR_SPR
"Optional title"
coid,  pid_s,  pid_m,  csysid
R,  h,  m,  f_n^max,  f_t^max,  d_n^max,  d_t^max,  ξ_n
ξ_t,  a_1,  a_2,  a_3
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
coid           : SPR connector ID
pid_s          : Slave part ID
pid_m          : Master part ID
csysid         : Coordinate system ID defining location of rivet
R              : Rivet radius
h              : Rivet height
m              : Rivet mass
f_n^max        : Pull-out strength
f_t^max        : Shear strength
d_n^max        : Pull out failure displacement
d_t^max        : Shear failure displacement
ξ_n            : Dimensionless parameter controlling the shape of the force pull-out curve
ξ_t            : Dimensionless parameter controlling the shape of the force shear displacement curve
a_1, a_2, a_3  : Parameters defining the strength in directions between pure pull-out and pure shear

*CONNECTOR_SPRING
coid,  N_1,  N_2,  m,  k,  ξ,  F_fail,  direc,  l_0
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
coid           : Spring connector ID
N_1            : Node 1
N_2            : Node 2
m              : Mass
k              : Stiffness (force per unit distance of elongation) or a FUNCTION defining the elastic force versus elongation
ξ              : Fraction of critical damping or a FUNCTION defining the damping force versus elongation rate
F_fail         : Spring failure force
                 default: No failure
direc          : Spring force direction
                 options:
                 0 -> tension and compression
                 1 -> tension only
                 2 -> compression only
l_0            : Unloaded spring length
                 default: Same as initial spring length

*CONTACT
"Optional title"
ctid,  accuracy_level,  accuracy_edge
entype_1,  enid_1,  entype_2,  enid_2,  μ,  pfac,  t_beg,  t_end
merge,  ξ,  gid_0,  gid_1,  δ_0^offset,  δ_0^max,  δ^edge
fid_wear1,  fid_wear2,  fid_thermal,  α_edge,  one_way,  no_internal,  σ_stick,  fric_heat
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
ctid           : Contact ID
accuracy_level : Accuracy level
                 options:
                 1  -> low
                 2  -> standard
                 > 2-> high
                 default: 2
accuracy_edge  : Flag to activate increased accuracy at sharp edges
                 options:
                 0 -> standard accuracy
                 1 -> increased accuracy
entype_1       : Entity type of Surface 1
                 options: P, PS, ALL
enid_1         : Entity identification number of Surface 1
entype_2       : Entity type of Surface 2
                 options: P, PS, ALL
enid_2         : Entity identification number of Surface 2
μ              : Coulomb coefficient of friction or FUNCTION (see example below)
                 options: constant, fcn
                 default: 0
pfac           : Penalty stiffness (contact pressure per unit distance of penetration)
                 default: automatic calculaton of stiffness
t_beg          : Contact activation time
                 options: constant, fcn
                 default: 0
t_end          : Contact deactivation time
                 options: constant, fcn
                 default: 1.0e20
merge          : Flag to activate merged faces in the contact
                 options:
                 0 -> merged faces are inactive
                 1 -> merged faces are active
ξ              : Fraction of critical damping
                 default: 0.1
gid_0          : Faces outside the geometry at time 0 are excluded from the contact
                 default: not used
gid_1          : Faces moving outside the geometry are deactivated from the contact
                 default: not used
δ_0^offset     : Maximum penetration offset for faces that are in contact at time zero. The offset is used to prevent unwanted contact forces
                 default: 0
δ_0^max        : Maximum initial penetration that is allowed. Faces penetrating more than δ_max at time 0 are released
δ^edge         : Penetration tolerance for sliding across sharp edges
                 default: 0
fid_wear1      : ID of a FUNCTION defining the contact wear rate of Surface 1
                 default: no wear calculation
fid_wear2      : ID of a FUNCTION defining the contact wear rate of Surface 2
                 default: no wear calculation
fid_thermal    : ID of a FUNCTION defining the thermal contact conductivity
                 default: no contact heat transfer
α_edge         : Angle defining a sharp edge (minimum angle between adjacent element faces)
                 default: 20 deg
one_way        : Flag to switch from symmetric to one way contact
                 options:
                 0 -> symmetric contact
                 1 -> one way contact
no_internal    : Flag to disable contact surface updates at element erosion or node splitting
                 options:
                 0 -> internal element faces are included
                 1 -> internal element faces are excluded
σ_stick        : Optional sticking failure stress
                 default: no contact sticking
fric_heat      : Flag to activate conversion of friction work to heat
                 options:
                 0 -> friction work is not converted to heat
                 1 -> friction work is converted to heat

*CONTACT_ACCURACY
"Optional title"
coid,  entype,  enid,  accuracy_level,  accuracy_edge
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
coid           : Command ID
entype         : Entity type
                 options: G, P, PS, ALL
enid           : Entity identification number
accuracy_level : Accuracy level
                 options:
                 1 -> low
                 2 -> standard
                 2 -> high
                 default: 2
accuracy_edge  : Flag to activate increased accuracy at sharp edges
                 options:
                 0 -> standard accuracy
                 1 -> increased accuracy

*CONTACT_REBAR
"Optional title"
switch 0: off, 1: on
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
switch         : Switch to activate contact between rebars and Finite Elements
                 options:
                 0 -> off
                 1 -> on

*COORDINATE_SYSTEM
"Optional title"
csysid,  x_0,  y_0,  z_0,  pid,  curve
x_x,  x_y,  x_z,  y_x,  y_y,  y_z
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
csysid         : Unique identification number
x_0, y_0, z_0  : Initial coordinate of origin
pid            : Optional part ID
                 default: not used
curve          : Flag to activate generation of CURVE files
                 options:
                 0 -> curve file output inactive
                 1 -> curve file output active
x_x, x_y, x_   z: Initial direction of local x-axis
y_x, y_y, y_   z: Vector needed for the definition of the local y- and z-axis

*COORDINATE_SYSTEM_CYLINDRICAL
"Optional title"
csysid,  x_0,  y_0,  z_0
z_x,  z_y,  z_z,  R_0x,  R_0y,  R_0z
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
csysid         : Unique identification number
x_0            : X-cordinate of a point on the cylinder axis
y_0            : Y-cordinate of a point on the cylinder axis
z_0            : Z-cordinate of a point on the cylinder axis
z_x            : X-component of axial direction
z_y            : Y-component of axial direction
z_z            : Z-component of axial direction
R_0x           : X-component of radial direction at θ=0
R_0y           : Y-component of radial direction at θ=0
R_0z           : Z-component of radial direction at θ=0

*COORDINATE_SYSTEM_FIXED
"Optional title"
csysid,  x_0,  y_0,  z_0
x_x,  x_y,  x_z,  y_x,  y_y,  y_z
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
csysid         : Unique identification number
x_0, y_0, z_0  : Coordinate of origin
x_x, x_y, x_z  : Direction of local x-axis
y_x, y_y, y_z  : Vector needed for the definition of the local y- and z-axis

*COORDINATE_SYSTEM_FUNCTION
"Optional title"
csysid,  x_0,  y_0,  z_0
x_x,  x_y,  x_z,  y_x,  y_y,  y_z
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
csysid         : Unique identification number
x_0, y_0, z_0  : Coordinate of origin
                 options: constant, fcn
x_x, x_y, x_z  : Direction of local x-axis
                 options: constant, fcn
y_x, y_y, y_z  : Vector needed for the definition of the local y- and z-axis
                 options: constant, fcn

*COORDINATE_SYSTEM_NODE
"Optional title"
csysid,  N_1,  N_2,  N_3
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
csysid         : Unique identification number
N_1, N_2, N_3  : Nodes defining the location and direction of the local system

