*END
This command is usually placed at the last line of every command file. 
All contents after this command will be automatically ignored by the solver.

*EOS_GRUNEISEN
eosid,  S,  Γ,  L
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
eosid          : Unique EOS identification number
S_1            : Linear Hugoniot slope coefficient
Gamma          : Gruneisen gamma
L              : Characteristic element size in shock viscosity calculation
                 default: automatically calculated

*EOS_TAIT
eosid,  γ
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
eosid          : Unique EOS identification number
γ              : Exponent in pressure-density relationship

*EROSION_CRITERION
coid
entype,  enid,  Δt^erode,  ε_geo^erode,  ε_v^erode,  ε_eff^p,  erode,  Δε_geo^erode,  T^erode
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
coid           : Command ID
entype         : Entity type
                 options: P, PS, ALL
enid           : Entity identification number
Δt^erode       : Time step size below which elements are eroded
                 default: not used
ε_geo^erode    : Effective deviatoric geometric strain above which elements are eroded
                 default: not used
ε_v^erode      : Volumetric strain above which elements are eroded
                 default: not used
ε_eff^p,erode  : Effective plastic strain above which elements are eroded
                 default: not used
Δε_geo^erode   : Incremental strain above which elements are eroded
                 default: 100.0
T^erode        : Temperature above which elements are eroded
                 default: not used

*EROSION_CRITERION_SPH_DRIVEN
"Optional title"
coid
pid, D^erode, ε_eff^(ᵖ,ᵉʳᵒᵈᵉ), R
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
coid           : Command ID
pid            : Part ID
D^erode        : Damage threshold for erosion
                 default: not used
ε_eff^(p,erode): Effective plastic strain threshold for erosion
                 default: not used
R              : Erosion radius
                 default: 0
   
*FRAGMENT_CLEANUP
"Optional title"
coid
pid,  t_clean,  m_min,  W_min
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
coid           : Command ID
pid            : Part ID
t_clean        : Clean-up time
m_min          : Minimum fragment mass
                 default: not used
W_min          : Minimum fragment kinetic energy
                 default: not used

*FREQUENCY_CUTOFF
"Optional title"
coid
entype,  enid,  Δt_target,  sf_cap,  t_start,  t_end,  no_regms
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
coid           : Command ID
entype         : Entity type
                 options: P, PS, ALL
enid           : Entity identification number
Δt_target      : Target time step size (scalar value of function of time)
                 options: scalar or fcn
sf_cap         : Maximum increase of time step size (scale factor)
                 options: scalar or fcn
                 default: not used
t_start        : Activation time
t_end          : Deactivation time
                 default: 1.0e10
no_regms       : Flag to disable regular mass scaling of the parts that are treated by this command (see Δt_min in TIME)
                 options:
                 0 -> regular mass scaling is allowed
                 1 -> regular mass scaling is deactivated

*FUNCTION
"Optional title"
fid,  derivative,  f(0),  ḟ(0),  type_x,  type_y
expression
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
fid            : Function ID
derivative     : Function derivative level
                 options:
                 0 -> f(t)       = expression
                 1 -> ḟ(t)       = expression
                 2 -> f̈(t)       = expression
f(0)           : Function value at time 0 (used if derivative > 0)
ḟ(0)           : First derivative of function at time 0 (used if derivative = 2)
type_x         : Abscissa data type
                 options: time, strain, none
type_y         : Ordinate data type
                 options: time, disp, length, velo, acc, force, stress, strain, pressure, temp, energy, none
expression     : Analytical expression

*GENERATE_COMPONENT_DISTRIBUTION
"Optional title"
pid
gid,  ctype,  D,  L
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
mid            : Unique material identification number
pid            : Part ID of generated components
gid            : Geometry ID of region that will be filled with components
ctype          : Component type
                 options: 1 -> sphere
D              : Component diameter
L              : Component length (for now not used)

*GENERATE_PARTICLE_DISTRIBUTION
"Optional title"
sbdid
gid,  gid_f,  Δ,  Δ_f,  w,  s
gid_2,  sbdid_2
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
sbdid          : Default subdomain ID of generated particles
gid            : Geometry ID of region that will be filled with particles
gid_f          : Geometry ID of region with increased particle density (refined region)
                 default: not used
Δ              : Target particle spacing (default)
Δ_f            : Target particle spacing in refined region (fine)
w              : Width of transition zone from Δ_f to Δ
                 default: 20*Δ
s              : Smoothing length scale factor
                 default: 2.5
gid_2          : Geometry ID of region within which particles are assigned to subdomain sbdid_2
                 default: not used
sbdid_2        : Subdomain ID 2
                 default: not used

