*INITIAL_MATERIAL_DIRECTION_WRAP
"Optional title"
coid,  entype,  enid
x_0,  y_0,  z_0,  u_x,  u_y,  u_z,  α
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
coid           : Command ID
entype         : Entity type
                 options: P, PS
enid           : Entity ID
x_0, y_0, z_0  : Coordinate used for definition of the ply location
u_x, u_y, u_z  : Vector used for definition of the ply orientation
α              : Angle used for definition of fiber direction

*INITIAL_PLASTIC_STRAIN_FUNCTION
coid,  entype,  enid,  fid,  multi
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
coid           : Command ID
entype         : Entity type
                 options: P, PS, G, ALL
enid           : Entity ID
fid            : ID of FUNCTION defining the effective plastic strain as function of (x,y,z)
multi          : Treatment of multiple commands
                 options:
                 0 -> plastic strains from previous commands are overwritten
                 1 -> plastic strains from multiple commands are superposed

*INITIAL_STATE
eid,  etype,  ip,  mtype,  V_0
F_11,  F_12,  F_13
F_21,  F_22,  F_23
F_31,  F_32,  F_33
σ_11,  σ_22,  σ_33,  σ_12,  σ_23,  σ_31
ε_11,  ε_22,  ε_33,  ε_12,  ε_23,  ε_31
v_01,  ...,  v_08
v_09,  ...,  v_16
v_17,  ...,  v_24
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
eid            : Element ID
etype          : Element type
ip             : Integration point number
mtype          : Material type
V_0            : Integration point volume in undeformed state
F_11, F_12, F_13: Deformation gradient components
F_21, F_22, F_23: Deformation gradient components
F_31, F_32, F_33: Deformation gradient components
σ_11, σ_22, σ_33, σ_12, σ_23, σ_31: Stress components
ε_11, ε_22, ε_33, ε_12, ε_23, ε_31: Strain components
v_01, ..., v_08: State variables 1-8
v_09, ..., v_16: State variables 9-16
v_17, ..., v_24: State variables 17-24

*INITIAL_STATE_HAZ
entype_weld,  enid_weld,  entype_base,  enid_base,  cid_sigy,  cid_D0
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
entype_weld    : Weld entity type
                 options: P, PS, PATH
enid_weld      : Weld entity ID
entype_base    : Base material entity type
                 options: P, PS
enid_base      : Base material entity ID
cid_sigy       : ID of a CURVE or FUNCTION describing yield stress as function of the distance from the weld
                 default: not used
cid_D0         : ID of a CURVE or FUNCTION describing initial damage as function of the distance from the weld
                 default: not used

*INITIAL_STRESS_FUNCTION
entype,  enid,  fid_xx,  fid_yy,  fid_zz,  fid_xy,  fid_yz,  fid_zx
multi
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
entype         : Entity type
                 options: M, P, PS, SPH, RB
enid           : Entity ID
fid_xx         : ID of FUNCTION defining σ_xx as function of (x,y,z)
fid_yy         : ID of FUNCTION defining σ_yy as function of (x,y,z)
fid_zz         : ID of FUNCTION defining σ_zz as function of (x,y,z)
fid_xy         : ID of FUNCTION defining σ_xy as function of (x,y,z)
fid_yz         : ID of FUNCTION defining σ_yz as function of (x,y,z)
fid_zx         : ID of FUNCTION defining σ_zx as function of (x,y,z)
multi          : Treatment of multiple commands
                 options:
                 0 -> stresses from previous commands are overwritten
                 1 -> stresses from multiple commands are superposed
                 2 -> stress component with largest absolute value is kept

*INITIAL_TEMPERATURE
entype,  enid,  fid,  T
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
entype         : Entity type
                 options: N, P, PS, ALL
enid           : Entity identification number
fid            : ID of a FUNCTION defining the temperature field
T              : Constant temperature value (only used if fid=0)

*INITIAL_THICKNESS
nid,  thickness
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
nid            : Node ID
thickness      : Initial thickness

*INITIAL_VELOCITY
entype,  enid,  v_x0,  v_y0,  v_z0,  ω_x,  ω_y,  ω_z
x_0,  y_0,  z_0,  δv_x,  δv_y,  δv_z,  csysid
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
entype         : Entity type
                 options: N, NS, P, PS, ALL, G, DP, SPH
enid           : Entity identification number
v_x0           : Initial velocity in x-direction
                 options: constant, fcn
                 default: 0
v_y0           : Initial velocity in y-direction
                 options: constant, fcn
                 default: 0
v_z0           : Initial velocity in z-direction
                 options: constant, fcn
                 default: 0
ω_x, ω_y, ω_z  : Initial angular velocity vector
                 default: (0,0,0)
x_0, y_0, z_0  : Center of rotation
                 default: (0,0,0)
δ v_x, δ v_y, δ v_z: Gradient of velocity field
                 default: (0,0,0)
csysid         : Optional local coordinate system ID
                 default: not used

*LOAD_AIR_BLAST
"Optional title"
coid
entype,  enid,  mtnt,  x_c,  y_c,  z_c,  tabid,  diffract
toff,  ground,  t_end
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
coid           : Command ID
entype         : Entity type
                 options: P, PS, ALL
enid           : Entity ID
mtnt           : Charge size (kg TNT equivalent)
x_c            : Charge location (x-coordinate)
y_c            : Charge location (y-coordinate)
z_c            : Charge location (z-coordinate)
tabid          : ID of TABLE defining reflective surfaces
diffract       : Diffraction level
                 options:
                 0 -> no diffraction
                 1 -> diffraction around one corner
                 2 -> diffraction around two corners
                 default: no diffraction
toff           : Time offset flag
                 options:
                 0 -> no offset
                 1 -> time of arrival is offset to t=0
ground         : Reflecting ground
                 options: 0, X, Y, Z
                 default: no ground
t_end          : Deactivation time
                 default: not used

*LOAD_CENTRIFUGAL
"Optional title"
entype,  enid,  cid,  csysid,  t_beg,  t_end
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
entype         : Entity type
                 options: N, NS, P, PS
enid           : Entity identification number
cid            : ID of a CURVE or FUNCTION defining angular velocity versus time
csysid         : Local coordinate system ID
t_beg          : Start time
t_end          : End time
                 default: 1.0e10

*LOAD_DAMPING
"Optional title"
entype,  enid,  cid,  μ,  c_dec,  sf,  gid
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
entype         : Entity type
                 options: N, NS, P, PS, ALL, SPH
enid           : Entity ID
cid            : ID of a CURVE or FUNCTION defining the mass damping coefficient C versus time
μ              : Viscous damping coefficient
c_dec          : Viscous decay coefficient
sf             : Mass damping scale factor when moving away from equilibrium
                 default: 1
gid            : Optional ID of GEOMETRY
                 default: not used
#example
    *LOAD_DAMPING
    ALL, 0, 99, 100
    *FUNCTION
    99
    1.0e7
    *FUNCTION
    100
    1.0e-5
#end               

*LOAD_ELEMENT_SMOOTHING
"Optional title"
coid
entype,  enid,  t_dec
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
coid           : Command ID
entype         : Entity type
                 options: P, PS, G, GS, FS, ALL
enid           : Entity identification numbe
t_dec          : Smoothing time parameter
                 default: Automatic calculation based on element time step size
#example
    *LOAD_ELEMENT_SMOOTHING
    "rubber block"
    1
    P, 1, 1.0e-3
#end               

*LOAD_EM_CABLE
"Optional title"
coid
pid_1,  pid_2,  fid_1,  fid_2
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
coid           : Command ID
pid_1          : Part ID of first cable
pid_2          : Part ID of second cable
fid_1          : Electrical current function for first cable
fid_2          : Electrical current function for second cable

*LOAD_FORCE
"Optional title"
coid
entype,  enid,  direc,  cid,  sf,  csysid,  t_beg,  t_end
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
coid           : Command ID (optional)
entype         : Entity type (P only for rigid bodies)
                 options: N, NS, G, FS, P
enid           : Entity identification number
direc          : Force/moment direction
                 options: X, Y, Z, RX, RY, RZ
cid            : ID of a CURVE or FUNCTION defining force/moment versus time
sf             : Force/moment scale factor
                 default: 1
csysid         : Local coordinate system ID
                 default: global coordinates are used
t_beg          : Start time
t_end          : End time
                 default: 1.0e10

*LOAD_FORCE_INTERACT
"Optional title"
coid
entype_1,  enid_1,  entype_2,  enid_2,  fid,  dtype,  dynamic
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
coid           : Command ID (optional)
entype_1       : Entity type of first body
                 options: P, PS
enid_1         : Entity identification number of first body
entype_2       : Entity type of second body
                 options: P, PS
fid            : Force FUNCTION
dtype          : Definiton of distance between bodies
                 options:
                 0 -> force based on distance between neareast elements
                 1 -> force based on distance between centers of gravity
dynamic        : Flag to activate dynamic search for nearest elements
                 options:
                 0 -> use nereast elements from time zero
                 1 -> use current geometry

*LOAD_GRAVITY
"Optional title"
direc,  cid,  addmass,  csysid,  sf
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
direc          : Direction for gravity loading
                 options: X, Y, Z
cid            : ID of a CURVE or FUNCTION defining gravity coefficient versus time
addmass        : Exclude added mass due to mass scaling from gravity loading
                 options:
                 0 -> include added mass
                 1 -> exclude added mass
csysid         : Optional local coordinate system ID
sf             : Optional gravity scale factor
                 default: 1
#example
    *LOAD_GRAVITY
    Z, 1
    *FUNCTION
    1
    9.81
#end               

*LOAD_PRESSURE
"Optional title"
coid
entype,  enid,  fid,  sf,  t_beg,  t_end,  csysid,  gid_SPH
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
coid           : Command ID (optional)
entype         : Entity type
                 options: P, PS, G, GS, FS, SPH, ALL
enid           : Entity identification number
fid            : ID of a CURVE or FUNCTION defining the pressure load
sf             : Pressure curve scale factor or FUNCTION (fcn)
                 default: 1
t_beg          : Start time
                 default: 0
t_end          : End time
                 default: 1.0e10
csysid         : Optional coordinate system ID. If defined, only surfaces visible from its origin are exposed to the pressure load
                 default: not used
gid_SPH        : ID of a GEOMETRY enclosing included SPH particles (entype = SPH only)

*LOAD_SHEAR
"Optional title"
entype,  enid,  cid_τ,  cid_vx,  cid_vy,  cid_vz,  t_beg,  t_end
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
