                 default: 1.0e20
cid_2          : D of an optional CURVE or FUNCTION f_2 defining the total thermal body load versus time (power)

*LOAD_THERMAL_RADIATION
"Optional title"
coid
entype,  enid,  T_amb,  d_max,  Δt_update
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
coid           : Command ID
entype         : Entity type
                 options: FS, G, GS, P, PS, ALL
enid           : Entity identification number
T_amb          : Ambient temperature
d_max          : Interaction cut-off distance
                 default: not used
Δt_update     : Interaction list update interval
                 default: no update

*LOAD_THERMAL_SURFACE
"Optional title"
coid,  entype,  enid,  cid,  sf,  t_beg,  t_end,  erode
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
coid           : Command ID
entype         : Entity type
                 options: FS, G, GS, P, PS, ALL
enid           : Entity identification number
cid            : ID of a CURVE or FUNCTION defining the thermal surface load versus time (power/unit area)
sf             : Curve scale factor
                 default: 1
t_beg          : Start time
                 default: 0
t_end          : End time
                 default: 1.0e20
erode          : Flag to account fo element erosion and exposure of new free surfaces
                 options:
                 0 -> surface is not updated
                 1 -> surface is updated at element erosion

*LOAD_UNDEX
"Optional title"
coid
entype,  enid,  x_c,  y_c,  z_c,  gdir,  d
m_HE,  ρ_HE,  p_c,  v_c,  A,  B,  γ,  K_c
C_d,  E_d,  u̇_0
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
coid           : Command ID
entype         : Entity type
                 options: P, PS, G, GS, FS, ALL
enid           : Entity identification number
x_c, y_c, z_c  : Explosive charge location
gdir           : Gravity loading direction
                 options: X, Y, Z
d              : Water depth
mHE            : Mass of explosive charge
ρ_HE           : Density of explosive charge
p_c            : Charge pressure constan
v_c            : Charge velocity constant
A              : Charge constant (dimensionless)
B              : Charge constant (dimensionless)
γ              : Heat capacity ratio
K_c            : Adabatic charge constant
C_d            : Bubble migration drag coefficient
E_d            : Bubble migration exponent
                 default: 2
u_0            : Reference migration velocity
                 default: 1

*MAP
"Optional title"
coid,  n_1,  n_2,  n_3
x_1,  ...,  x_8
.
x_M,  ...,  x_N
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
coid           : Command ID
n_1            : Number of data points in direction 1 (rows if n_3 = 0)
n_2            : Number of data points in direction 2 (columns if n_3 = 0)
n_3            : Number of data points in direction 3 (optional)
x_1, ..., x_8  : Data points 1 to 8
.              : 
x_M, ..., x_N  : Data points M to N = n_1 times n_2 times n_3

*MAT_BB
"Optional title"
mid,  ρ,  K
μ_A,  λ_L,  r,  m,  q
μ_B,  b_0,  b_1,  b_2,  ξ,  σ_y,  ̇γ_0
W_c,  λ_f,  erode
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
mid            : Unique material identification number
ρ              : Density
K              : Bulk modulus
μ_A            : Initial shear stiffness of Network A
lambda_L       : Locking stretch
r              : Mullins damage parameter 1
                 default: not used
m              : Mullins damage parameter 2
                 default: not used
q              : Mullins damage parameter 3
                 default: not used
μ_B            : Initial shear stiffness of Network B
b_0            : Viscous flow stress parameter
b_1            : Viscous flow stress exponent 1
b_2            : Viscous flow stress exponent 2
ξ              : Small constant in viscous flow rate law
σ_y            : Yield stress (constant or function of effective visco-plastic strain)
                 options: constant, fcn
γ_0            : Reference strain rate
W_c            : Failure parameter
                 default: not used
lambda_f       : Failure stretch
                 default: not used
erode          : Element erosion flag
                 options:
                 0 -> failed element is not eroded
                 1 -> failed element is eroded

*MAT_BERGSTROM_BOYCE
"Optional title"
mid,  ρ,  K
μ,  λ_L,  a_0,  a_1,  η_max,  ̇γ_0,  ξ,  B
σ_0,  Q,  C,  m,  c_dec,  β,  W_c,  λ_f
b_0,  b_1,  b_2,  μ_B,  erode
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
mid            : Unique material identification number
ρ              : Density
K              : Bulk modulus
μ              : Initial shear stiffness of Network A
lambda_L       : Locking stretch
a_0            : Parameter driving damage in Network A
a_1            : Exponent driving damage in Network A
η_max          : Maximum damage in network A
γ_0            : Parameter in viscous flow law in Network B
ξ              : Small constant in viscous flow rate law in Network B
B              : Exponent in viscous flow law in Network B
σ_0            : Viscous flow stress parameter in Network B
Q              : Viscous hardening coefficient in Network B
C              : Viscous hardening exponent in Network B
m              : Viscous flow rate exponent in Network
c_dec          : Viscous decay parameter in Network B
β              : Pressure dependency parameter for viscous flow in Network B
W_c            : Failure parameter in Network B
                 default: not used
lambda_f       : Failure stretch
                 default: not used
b_0            : Viscous flow stress parameter in Network B
b_1            : Viscous flow stress exponent in Network B
μ_B            : Optional initial shear stiffness of Network B
                 default: not used
erode          : Optional initial shear stiffness of Network B
                 options:
                 0 -> shear stresses are set to zero at full damage
                 1 -> element is removed at full damage
                 2 -> node splitting at full damage
#example
    *MAT_BERGSTROM_BOYCE
    "rubber"
    1, 1100, 1.0e9
    1.4e6, 2.72, 0.6, 1, 0.95, 1
    0, 0, 0, 0, 1e-5
    800, 1, 1
#end               

*MAT_CABLE
"Optional title"
mid,  ρ,  E,  ν
E_t1,  E_t2,  E_tm,  ε_tf,  σ_ty
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
mid            : Unique material identification number
ρ              : Density
E              : Bulk modulus
ν              : Poisson's ratio
E_t1           : Tensile stiffness (linear term)
E_t2           : Tensile stiffness (quadratic term)
                 default: not used
E_tm           : Tensile stiffness (maximum)
                 default: not used
ε_tf           : Tensile fiber failure strain
                 default: no failure
σ_ty           : Tensile fiber yield stress
                 default: no plasticty

*MAT_CERAMIC
"Optional title"
mid,  ρ,  G
A_0,  B_0,  A_f,  B_f,  ε_f,  σ_s,  t_s,  α_s
K_1,  K_2,  K_3,  β,  K_c,  σ_0^max,  σ_f^max
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
mid            : Unique material identification number
ρ              : Density
G              : Shear modulus
A_0            : Yield surface parameter
B_0            : Yield surface parameter
A_f            : Failure surface parameter
B_f            : Failure surface parameter
ε_f            : Volumetric crushing strain
σ_s            : Spall strength
                 default: A_0/2
t_s            : Time to develop spall fracture at threshold stress
α_s            : Exponent controlling time to develop spall fracture
K_1            : Linear bulk stiffness term
K_2            : Quadratic bulk stiffness term
K_3            : Cubic bulk stiffness term
β              : Parameter controlling the plastic flow direction at crushing. β must be larger than 0 and can not exceed 1.
                 default: 1 -> associated plastic flow
K_c            : Fracture toughness
                 default: not used
σ_0^max        : Shear strength cap of undamaged material
                 default: not used
σ_f^max        : Shear strength cap of fully damaged material
                 default: not used

*MAT_CONCRETE_2018
"Optional title"
mid,  ρ,  G
K_0,  K_L,  p_0,  p_L,  ε_L,  n,  f_t,  f_c
r_f,  r_e,  ε_t,  ε_c,  c,  c_dec,  ξ,  bulk
K_Ic
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
mid            : Unique material identification number
ρ              : Density
G              : Shear modulus
K_0            : Initial bulk modulus
K_L            : Bulk modulus at full compaction
p_0            : Hydrostatic pressure at crush limit
p_L            : Hydrostatic pressure at full compaction
ε_L            : Volumetric strain at full compaction
n              : Exponent controlling the shape of the compaction curve
                 default: 1
f_t            : Uniaxial tensile strength
f_c            : Uniaxial compressive strength
r_f            : Strain rate parameter
r_e            : Strain rate parameter
ε_t            : Uni-axial tensile failure strain
ε_c            : Volumetric crushing failure strain
c              : Viscosity parameter
c_dec          : Viscous decay coefficient
                 default: not used
ξ              : Dimensionless parameter controlling the shape of the yield surface cap
                 default: ξ = f_c/2p_0
bulk           : Flag to activate bulking
                 options:
                 0 -> no bulking
                 1 -> bulking activated
K_Ic           : Fracture toughness
#example
    *PARAMETER_DEFAULT
    rho = 2310  , "Density", 0, density
    fc  = 55.0e6, "Uniaxial compressive strength", 0, stress
    ft  = 4.0e6 , "Uniaxial tensile strength", 0, stress
    *MAT_CONCRETE_2018
    1, %rho, 16.0e9
    25.0e9, 40.0e9, 75.0e6, 500.0e6, 0.1, 2.0, %ft, %fc
    2.5e6, 0.3, 0.005, 0.025, 1.0e5, 0.0, 0.8, 0.0
    2.5e6
#end

*MAT_CONCRETE_2021
"Optional title"
mid,  ρ,  G
K_0,  K_L,  p_0,  p_L,  ε_L,  n,  f_t,  f_c
S_max,  e,  ξ,  b,  r,  s,  c_dev,  c_vol
v,  ξ_y,  ε_ut,  ε_uc,  G_t,  G_c,  ε_fc,  nsplit
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
mid            : Unique material identification number
ρ              : Density
G              : Shear modulus
K_0            : Initial bulk modulus
K_L            : Bulk modulus at full compaction
p_0            : Hydrostatic pressure at crush limit
p_L            : Hydrostatic pressure at full compaction
ε_L            : Volumetric strain at full compaction
n              : Exponent controlling the shape of the compaction curve
                 default: 1
f_t            : Uniaxial tensile strength
f_c            : Uniaxial compressive strength
e              : Yield surface eccentricity parameter
ξ              : Dimensionless parameter controlling the shape of the yield surface cap
                 default: ξ = f_c/2p_0
b              : Bulking parameter ranging between 0 and 1
                 default: no bulking
r              : Strain rate hardening parameter
s              : Strain rate hardeing exponent
c_dev          : Deviatoric viscosity parameter
c_vol          : Compressive viscosity parameter
v              : Viscosity exponent
ξ_y            : Ratio between yield stress and maximum flow stress
ε_ut           : Strain at maximum stress in uni-axial tension
ε_uc           : Strain at maximum stress in uni-axial compression
G_t            : Fracture energy in uni-axial tension
G_c            : Fracture energy in uni-axial compression
ε_fc           : Crushing failure strain
nsplit         : Node splitting activation flag
                 options:
                 0 -> node splitting inactive
                 1 -> node splitting active

