*MAT_JC_FIELD
"Optional title"
mid,  ρ,  E,  ν
A,  B,  n,  C,  m,  T_0,  T_m,  ̇ε_0
C_p,  k,  W_c0,  c_1,  c_2,  erode
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
mid            : Unique material identification number
ρ              : Density
E              : Young's modulus
ν              : Poisson's ratio
A              : Initial yield strength
B              : Hardening parameter
n              : Hardening parameter
C              : Strain rate hardening parameter
m              : Thermal softening parameter
T_0            : Ambient temperature
T_m            : Melting temperature
ε_0            : Strain rate parameter
                 default: 1
C_p            : Specific heat capacity
k              : Plastic work to heat conversion factor
                 default: 0.9
W_c0           : Cockcroft-Latham damage parameter
                 default: damage not active
c_1            : Extended rate dependency parameter to the Cockcroft-Latham damage criterion
                 default: not active
c_2            : Extended rate dependency parameter to the Cockcroft-Latham damage criterion
                 default: not active
erode          : Element erosion flag
                 options:
                 0 -> failed elements keep the bulk stiffness
                 1 -> failed elements are eroded
                 2 -> node splitting
#example
    *MAT_JC_FIELD
    1, 7800.0, 210.0e9, 0.3
    fcn(10), 2.0e8, 0.3
    0, 0, fcn(20), 2
    *FUNCTION
    10
    1.0e9*crv(11,dist_surf(0, 0, 1))
    *FUNCTION
    20
    4.0e8*crv(21,dist_surf(0, 0, 1))
#end               

