A_r,  B_r,  R_1,  r,  R_2,  r,  ω_r,  e_0,  r,  p_0
a,  b,  c,  d,  e,  g,  I,  x
y,  z,  F_1,  F_2,  F_3,  G_1,  G_2,  L
c_vr,  c_vu,  c_pu
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
mid            : Unique material identification number
ρ_0            : Initial density
G              : Shear modulus (unreacted material)
A              : Initial yield strength (unreacted material)
B              : Hardening parameter (unreacted material)
n              : Hardening exponent (unreacted material)
A_u            : JWL coefficient (unreacted material)
B_u            : JWL coefficient (unreacted material)
R_1,u          : JWL coefficient (unreacted material)
R_2,u          : JWL coefficient (unreacted material)
ω_u            : JWL coefficient (unreacted material)
A_r            : JWL coefficient (reacted material)
B_r            : JWL coefficient (reacted material)
R_1,r          : JWL coefficient (reacted material)
R_2,r          : JWL coefficient (reacted material)
ω_r            : JWL coefficient (reacted material)
e_0,r          : Initial specific internal energy (reacted material)
p_0            : Reference pressure
                 default: p_ref = 1
a              : Threshold compression for ignition (stage I)
b              : Reaction rate exponent (stage I)
c              : Reaction rate shape exponent (stage II)
d              : Reaction rate shape exponent (stage II)
e              : Reaction rate shape exponent (stage III)
g              : Reaction rate shape exponent (stage III)
I              : Reaction rate factor (stage I)
x              : Reaction rate exponent (stage I)
y              : Reaction rate pressure exponent (stage II)
z              : Reaction rate pressure exponent (stage III)
F_1            : Reaction rate level (stage I)
F_2            : Reaction rate level (stage II)
F_3            : Reaction rate level (stage III)
G_1            : Reaction rate factor (stage II)
G_2            : Reaction rate factor (stage III)
L              : Fixed element size in shock viscosity pressure calculation
                 default: local element size

*MAT_METAL
"Optional title"
mid,  ρ,  E,  ν,  did,  thpid,  eosid
cid,  ξ,  tresca,  c,  ̇ε_0,  m,  T_0,  T_m
s_0,  s_1,  ε_d,  μ
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
mid            : Unique material identification number
ρ              : Density
E              : Young's modulus
ν              : Poisson's ratio
did            : Damage property command ID
thpid          : Thermal property command ID
eosid          : Equation-of-state ID
cid            : ID of a CURVE or FUNCTION defining effective plastic flow stress versus plastic strain (equivalent measures)
ξ              : Kinematical hardening parameter ranging from 0 to 1 (FE only)
                 default: 0 (pure iso-tropic hardening)
yield          : Yield criteria option (FE only)
                 options:
                 =0  -> von Mises (used for SPH)
                 =1  -> Tresca
                 >=2 -> Hosford with exponent yield
c              : Strain rate hardening parameter
                 default: 0
ε_0            : Reference strain rate
                 default: 1
m              : Thermal softening parameter
                 default: thermal softening deactivated
T_0            : Thermal softening reference temperature
                 default: 0
T_m            : Melting temperature
                 default: 1.0e20
s_0            : Damage softening parameter (threshold damage level)
                 default: not used
s_1            : Damage softening parameter
ε_d            : Dilatation (void fraction) at full damage
μ              : Optional rate parameter
                 default: not used
res^SPH        : Residual relative strength of fully damaged material (SPH only)
                 default: 0 (no strength)
sf_D^SPH       : Damage evolution scale factor for SPH nodes located at crack tips (SPH only)
                 default: 1 (no scaling)
#example
    *MAT_METAL
    "Armco"
    1, 7800.0, 210.0e9, 0.3, 1, 1, 1
    1, 0, 0, 0.042, 1.0, 0.46, 293.0, 1800.0
    *FUNCTION
    1
    167.0e6 + 415.0e6 * epsp^0.3
    *PROP_DAMAGE_CL
    1
    3.2e9, 5000.0
    0, 0.0
    *PROP_THERMAL
    1, 0, 450.0, 0, 0, 293.0
    *EOS_GRUNEISEN
    1, 1.5, 2.0
    
#end

*MAT_MMC
Has been renamed to MAT_MM_CERAMIC

*MAT_MMC_OST
Has been renamed to MAT_MM_OST_CERAMIC

*MAT_MM_CERAMIC
"Optional title"
mid,  ρ,  G
σ_c,  σ_x,  P_x,  σ_cap,  α,  ε_p_fail,  yield
K,  β,  ε_v_max,  c,  ̇ε_0,  ψ,  d,  d_dec
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
mid            : Unique material identification number
ρ              : Density
G              : Shear modulus
σ_c            : Uniaxial compressive strength
σ_x            : Compressive strength at pressure x
P_x            : Pressure x
σ_cap          : Cap on yield surface
                 default: 1.0e20
α              : Failed-to-intact material strength ratio
ε_p,fail       : Effective plastic strain at failure
yield          : Yield criteria option (FE only) 
                 options: 
                 0.0 -> von Mises (used for SPH) 
                 1.0 -> Rankine
K              : Bulk modulus
β              : Bulking parameter ranging between 0 and 1
                 default: 0 (no bulking)
ε_v,max        : Cap on volumetric strain of bulking
                 default: not used
c              : Strain rate parameter
ε_0            : Reference strain rate
psi            : Parameter controlling the rate dependency on the hydrostatic tensile strength
                 default: 0.0 (no rate effects on hydrostatic tensile strength)
d              : Damping coefficient
d_dec          : Damping decay coefficient
#example
    *MAT_MM_CERAMIC
    1, 3200, 198.3e9
    3.87e9, 6.32e9, 2.39e9, 15.0e9, 0.6, 0.0, 0.0
    225.5e9, 0.0, 0.0, 0.03, 1.0e-2, 0.0, 1.0e3, 1.0e-8
#end

*MAT_MM_CONCRETE
"Optional title"
mid,  ρ,  G
K_0,  K_L,  cid_cmp,  f_t,  f_c,  ξ,  λ,  γ
ξ_y,  ξ_r,  ε_p,  u0,  ε_p,  r0,  ψ_p,  ψ_r,  ε_p,  u^min,  ε_p,  r^min
m,  bulk,  bulk_cap,  cid_src,  cid_srt,  c,  σ_y,  min,  σ_y,  max
μ,  G_r0,  L_ref,  nsplit
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
mid            : Unique material identification number
ρ              : Density
G              : Shear modulus
K_0            : Bulk modulus of intact material
K_L            : Bulk modulus at full compaction
cid_cmp        : ID of CURVE with pressure vs. inelastic volumetric strain
f_t            : Uniaxial tensile strength
f_c            : Uniaxial compressive strength
ξ              : Parameter controlling transition between region 2 to 3
                 default: 0.5
lambda         : Parameter controlling strength in region 2 and 3
                 default: 0.5
γ              : Lode parameter dependency ( = 0 -> Rankine, = 1 -> von Mises)
ξ_y            : Parameter controlling initial yield surface
ξ_r            : Parameter controlling residual surface
ε_p,u0         : Transition strain from initial yield surface to ultimate surface (at p = f_c/3)
ε_p,r0         : Transition strain from ultimate surface to residual surface (at p = f_c/3)
psi_p          : Pressure dependency on transition strains
                 default: not used
psi_r          : Strain rate dependency on transition strains
                 default: not used
ε_p,u^min      : Lower cap on ε_p,u
                 default: not used
ε_p,r^min      : Lower cap on ε_p,r
                 default: not used
m              : Exponent on damage factor
                 default: 1
bulk           : Bulking parameter ranging between 0 and 1
                 default: not used
bulk_cap       : Cap on volumetric strain caused by bulking
                 default: not used
cid_src        : ID of CURVE with stress vs. plastic strain rate (at p ge f_c/3)
cid_srt        : ID of CURVE with stress vs. plastic strain rate (at p le -f_t/3)
c              : Viscous damping coefficient
                 default: not used
σ_y,min        : Lower cap on flow stress
                 default: not used
σ_y,max        : Upper cap on flow stress
                 default: not used
μ              : Deviation from nominal values
                 default: not used
G_r0           : Energy per unit area in transition from ultimate to residual surface (at p = f_c/3)
                 default: not used
L_ref          : Reference element length
                 default: not used
erode          : Element erosion flag
                 options:
                 0 -> failed element is not eroded
                 1 -> node splitting at failure
                 2 -> failed element is eroded         

*MAT_MM_OST_CERAMIC
"Optional title"
mid,  ρ_0,  G
σ_c,  σ_x,  p_x,  σ_cap,  c_1_f,  σ_cap_f,  ε_p_f,  s
K_1,  K_2,  K_3,  yield,  β,  ε_v_max,  c,  ̇ε_0
ψ,  d,  d_dec,  nsplit
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
mid            : Unique material identification number
ρ_0            : Density
G              : Shear modulus
σ_c            : Uniaxial compressive strength
σ_x            : Compressive strength at pressure x
p_x            : Pressure x
σ_cap          : Upper bound for yield surface
                 default: 1.0e20 
c_1,f          : Flow stress pressure hardening parameter for failed material
σ_cap,f        : Upper bound for flow stress of failed material
                 default: 1.0e20 
ε_p,f          : Effective plastic strain at failure
                 options: constant, fcn
s              : Tensile damage softening exponent
                 default: no damage softening
K_1            : Linear bulk stiffness term
K_2            : Quadratic bulk stiffness term
K_3            : Cubic bulk stiffness term
yield          : Yield criteria option (FE only)
                 options:
                 0.0 -> von Mises
                 1.0 -> Rankine
β              : Bulking parameter ranging between 0 and 1
                 default: 0.0 (no bulking)
ε_v,max        : Cap on volumetric strain of bulking
                 default: not used
c              : Strain rate parameter
ε_0            : Reference strain rate
psi            : Parameter controlling the rate dependency on the hydrostatic tensile strength
                 default: 0.0 (no rate effects on hydrostatic tensile strength)
d              : Damping coefficient
d_dec          : Damping decay coefficient
nsplit         : Node splitting activation flag
                 options:
                 0 -> node splitting inactive
                 1 -> node splitting active
#example
    *PARAMETER
    rho       = 3200   , "Density", 0, density
    G         = 198.3e9, "Shear modulus", 0, stress
    sig_c     = 3.87e9 , "Uniaxial compressive strength", 0, stress
    sig_x     = 6.32e9 , "Compressive strength at pressure x", 0, stress
    p_x       = 2.39e9 , "Pressure x", 0, pressure
    sig_cap   = 15.0e9 , "Cap on yield surface", 0, stress
    alpha     = 0.6    , "Failed-to-intact material strength ratio", 0, none
    epsp_fail = 0.0    , "Effective plastic strain at failure", 0, strain
    yield     = 0.0    , "Type of yield surface (= 0.0 -> von Mises, = 1.0 -> Rankine)", 0, none
    K         = 225.5e9, "Bulk modulus", 0, pressure
    beta      = 0.0    , "Parameter controlling the direction of plastic flow", 0, none
    epsv_max  = 0.0    , "Cap on volumetric strain of bulking", 0, strain
    c         = 0.03   , "Strain rate parameter", 0, none
    eps0      = 1.0e-2 , "Reference strain rate", 0, srate
    psi       = 0.0    , "Parameter controlling the rate dependency on the hydrostatic tensile strength", 0, none
    d         = 1.0e3  , "Damping coefficient", 0, viscosity
    d_dec     = 1.0e-8 , "Damping decay coefficient", 0, time
    *MAT_MM_CERAMIC
    1, %rho, %G
    %sig_c, %sig_x, %p_x, %sig_cap, %alpha, %epsp_fail, %yield
    %K, %beta, %epsv_max, %c, %eps0, %psi, %d, %d_dec
#end             


*MAT_MOONEY_RIVLIN
"Optional title"
mid,  ρ,  K,  .,  .,  thpid
C_1,  C_2,  α_1,  β_1,  α_2,  β_2,  α_3,  β_3
α_4,  β_4
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
mid            : Unique material identification number
ρ              : Density
K              : Bulk modulus
.              : Not used
.              : Not used
thpid          : Thermal property ID
C_1            : Shear stiffness parameter
C_2            : Shear stiffness parameter
α_1            : Viscous stiffness parameter
β_1            : Viscous decay parameter
α_2            : Viscous stiffness parameter
β_2            : Viscous decay parameter
α_3            : Viscous stiffness parameter
β_3            : Viscous decay parameter
α_4            : Viscous stiffness parameter
β_4            : Viscous decay parameter
#example
    *MAT_MOONEY_RIVLIN
    "Calf flesh"
