*MAT_VISCOUS_FOAM
"Optional title"
mid,  ρ,  E_1
η,  cid_fe,  cid_fv,  c_dec,  σ_cut,  γ,  ε_f,  G_2
σ_y
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
mid            : Unique material identification number
ρ              : Density
E_1            : Young's modulus for network 1 of fully compacted foam
η              : Initial porosity (between 0 and 1)
cid_fe         : ID of elastic compaction stress curve (f^e)
cid_fv         : ID of viscous stress curve (f^v)
c_dec          : Viscous decay parameter
σ_cut          : Tensile cut-off stress
γ              : Hysteresis parameter
ε_f            : Optional plastic failure strain in tension
G_2            : Shear modulus of optional network 2
σ_y            : Yield stress (von Mises) of optional network 2
#example
    *MAT_VISCOUS_FOAM
    1, 150, 1e8
    0.7, 99
    *CURVE
    "stress-compaction curve"
    99
    0.0,   0.0
    0.01,  1.0e5
    0.015, 1.3e5
    0.02,  1.5e5
    0.025, 1.6e5
    0.5,   2.6e5
    0.6,   3.7e5
    0.65,  7.8e5
    0.7,   2.2e6
#end

