*MERGE
"Optional title"
coid
entype_s,  enid_s,  entype_m,  enid_m,  tol,  mfid,  gid,  penalty,  α_max,  no_self
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
coid           : Command ID (optional)
entype_s       : Slave entity type
                 options: G, NS, P, PS, SPH
enid_s         : Slave entity identification number
entype_m       : Master entity type
                 options: G, P, PS
enid_m         : Master entity identification number
tol            : Tolerance for merging (absolute distance)
                 default: 1% of the master face side length
mfid           : ID of MERGE_FAILURE command
                 default: no failure
gid            : ID of GEOMETRY defining the region to be merged
                 default: no geometry
penalty        : Flag to switch to penalty formulation
                 options:
                 0 -> constraint based
                 1 -> penalty based
α_max          : Maximum allowed deviation from parallelism
                 default: 25^circ
no_self        : Flag to deactivate self-merging (same slave and master part ID)
                 options:
                 0 -> self-merge is allowed
                 1 -> self-merge is deactivated

*MERGE_DUPLICATED_NODES
entype_s,  enid_s,  entype_m,  enid_m,  tol,  refine
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
entype_s       : Slave entity type
                 options: P, PS
enid_s         : Slave entity identification number
entype_m       : Master entity type
                 options: P, PS
enid_m         : Master entity identification number
tol            : Tolerance for merging nodes
                 default: 0
refine         : Flag to merge duplicated nodes before mesh refinement (see REFINE)
                 options:
                 0 -> After mesh refinement
                 1 -> Before mesh refinement

*MERGE_FAILURE_BOLT
mfid,  T_fail,  S_fail,  n_T,  n_S
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
mfid           : Merge failure command ID
T_fail         : Tensile failure force
S_fail         : Shear failure force
n_T            : Tensile failure exponent
                 default: n_T=2
n_S            : Shear failure exponent
                 default: n_S=2

*MERGE_FAILURE_COHESIVE
mfid,  σ_fail,  τ_fail,  G_I,  G_II,  Δ_ref
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
mfid           : Merge failure command ID
σ_fail         : Tensile failure stress
tau_fail       : Shear failure stres
G_I            : Optional modus I energy per unit area
G_II           : Optional modus II energy per unit area
Δ_ref          : OPtional element reference size

*MERGE_FAILURE_FORCE
mfid,  T_fail,  S_fail,  n_T,  n_S
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
mfid           : Merge failure command ID
T_fail         : Tensile failure force
S_fail         : Shear failure force
n_T            : Tensile failure exponent
                 default: n_T=2
n_S            : Shear failure exponent
                 default: n_s=2_

