variant        : Variant number
revision       : Optional revision number
sf_x, sf_y, sf_z: Scale factors for nodal coordinates in x, y and z directions
                 default: 1
nid_offset     : Number to add to all node IDs
eid_offset     : Number to add to all element IDs
pid_offset     : Number to add to all part IDs
mid_offset     : Number to add to all material, damage, EOS and thermal property command IDs
gid_offset     : Number to add to all other command IDs
x_0, y_0, z_0  : Start point for mesh translation
x_1, y_1, z_1  : End point for mesh translation
x_x, x_y, x_z  : New direction of x-axis
                 default: (1,0,0)
y_x, y_y, y_z  : New direction of y-axis
                 default: (0,1,0)
param = expression: Parameter name and an expression defining its value
description    : Optional parameter description

*OUTPUT
Δt_imp,  Δt_ascii,  Δt_db,  fragment
nfilter,  efilter,  entype_res,  enid_res,  N_res
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
Δt_imp         : Output interval for complete model data (.imp-files)
                 default: Δt_imp= t_term/100
Δt_ascii       : Output interval for ASCII data (.out-files)
                 default: Δt_ascii=t_term/1000
Δt_db          : Output interval for model database and state files. No database or state files 
                 will be output if Δt_db is larger than t_term (see TIME)
                 default: a database file is generated at t_term
fragment       : Flag to activate fragment list generation
                 options:
                 0 -> no fragment list generation (default)
                 1 -> FE fragment list is written to .imp-database
                 2 -> SPH fragment list is written to .imp-database
                 3 -> FE and SPH fragment list is written to .imp-database
nfilter        : Filter for node and discrete particle data that will be written to impetus.imp
                 options:
                 0 -> output all node data (default)
                 1 -> output displacements only
                 2 -> do not output discrete particles
efilter        : Filter for element data that will be written to impetus.imp
                 options:
                 0 -> output all element data (default)
                 1 -> output effective stress, plastic strain and damage
                 2 -> output no element data
entype_res     : Entity type for state file output. The state file is an ASCII file in command 
                 format containing elements, nodes (coordinates and velocities) and contact 
		 information. Stresses, strains and state variables are output to a separate binary file.
                 options: P, PS, ALL
                 default: no state file
enid_res       : Entity ID for state file output
N_res          : Number of cyclic alternating files for model database and state file output
                 options: 1 leq N_res leq 99
                 default: N_res=9

*OUTPUT_CONTACT_FORCE
"Optional title"
coid,  entype,  enid
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
coid           : Command ID
entype         : Slave entity type
                 options: P, PS, G, ALL
enid           : Entity ID

*OUTPUT_DAMAGE_MAP
"Optional title"
coid
pid,  N_x,  N_y,  N_z,  csysid
x_0,  y_0,  z_0,  x_1,  y_1,  z_1
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
coid           : Command ID
pid            : ID of part from which data will be mapped at termination time
N_x            : Number of data points in local x-direction
N_y            : Number of data points in local y-direction
N_z            : Number of data points in local z-direction
csysid         : Optional local coordinate system ID
                 default: global coordinates are used
x_0            : Mapping domain minimum x-coordinate
y_0            : Mapping domain minimum y-coordinate
z_0            : Mapping domain minimum z-coordinate
x_1            : Mapping domain maximum x-coordinate
y_1            : Mapping domain maximum y-coordinate
z_1            : Mapping domain maximum z-coordinate

*OUTPUT_DEBUG
message
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
message        : Debug message

*OUTPUT_ELEMENT
entype,  enid
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
entype         : Entity type
                 options: E, ES
enid           : Entity identification number

*OUTPUT_ERROR
error
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
error          : Error message

*OUTPUT_FORMING
form
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
form           : Flag to activate output of sheet thickness
                 options:
                 0 -> do not output sheet thickness
                 1 -> output sheet thickness

*OUTPUT_J_INTEGRAL
"Optional title"
coid,  entype,  enid,  csysid,  R,  b
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
coid           : Command ID
entype         : Entity type
                 options: P, PS, ALL
enid           : Entity ID
csysid         : Local coordinate system ID
R              : Integral path radius
b              : Crack width
                 default: local component thickness

*OUTPUT_NODE
entype,  enid
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
entype         : Entity type
                 options: N, NS
enid           : Entity identification number

*OUTPUT_SECTION
"Optional title"
coid,  entype,  enid,  csysid,  R
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
coid           : Command ID
entype         : Entity type
                 options: P, PS, ALL
enid           : Entity ID
csysid         : Local coordinate system ID
R              : Section radius
                 default: not used

*OUTPUT_SENSOR
"Optional title"
sid,  pid,  x_0,  y_0,  z_0,  R,  csysid,  ref,  lagrange
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
sid            : Sensor ID
pid            : Sensor type or ID of part where the sensor is located
                 options: Part ID, DP (discrete particle), SPH, CFD or RB (rebar)
                 default: nearest part
x_0            : Initial x-coordinate of sensor
y_0            : Initial y-coordinate of sensor
z_0            : Initial z-coordinate of sensor
R              : Sensor sampling radius (DP) or maximum search distance (CFD)
csysid         : Optional local coordinate system ID
ref            : Reference system for velocity and displacement output
                 options:
                 0 -> Output displacement/velocity relative local coordinate system
                 1 -> Output displacement/velocity relative global origin
lagrange       : CFD and DP sensor flag to let the sensor follow the material flow
                 options:
                 0 -> Sensor fixed in space
                 1 -> Sensor follows material

*OUTPUT_SENSOR_EXTENDED
"Optional title"
coid
sid_0,  sid_1,  Δt_out,  fid_1,  ...,  fid_5
.
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
python_file_name: Name of python file
coid           : Command ID
sid_0          : ID of first sensor in range (see OUTPUT_SENSOR)
sid_1          : ID of last sensor in range (see OUTPUT_SENSOR)
Δt_out         : Output interval
                 default: Δt_out = Δt_ascii
fid_1, ..., fid_5: Optional functions used in sensor calculations
name_1         : Name of variable 1
name_2         : Name of variable 2
.              : 
name_n         : Name of variable n

*OUTPUT_SENSOR_PATH
"Optional title"
coid,  pid,  pathid,  N
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
coid           : Sensor ID
pid            : Marks is the sensors are attached to specific part or if they are embedded in the CFD domain
                 options: Part ID or CFD
pathid         : ID of PATH along which the sensors are positioned
N              : Number of sensors along the path (N geq 2)

*OUTPUT_SENSOR_THICKNESS
"Optional title"
coid,  pid,  x_0,  y_0,  z_0,  fixed,  t_beg,  t_end
n_x,  n_y,  n_z
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
coid           : Sensor ID
pid            : ID of part where the sensor is located
x_0            : Initial x-coordinate of sensor
y_0            : Initial y-coordinate of sensor
z_0            : Initial z-coordinate of sensor
fixed          : Flag to fix sensor in space
                 options:
                 0 -> sensor follows material
                 1 -> sensor is fixed in space
t_beg          : Sensor activation time
                 default: 0
t_end          : Sensor deactivation time
                 default: 1.0e20
n_x            : x-component of thickness measuring direction
                 default: not used
n_y            : y-component of thickness measuring direction
                 default: not used
n_z            : z-component of thickness measuring direction
                 default: not used

*OUTPUT_USER
"filename"
coid,  "name_a",  fcn_a,  type_a
"name_1", fcn_1, type_1
.
"name_n", fcn_n, type_n
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
filename       : File name for ASCII output (command ID and .out will be added as an extension)
coid           : Command ID
name_a         : Optional name of abscissa
                 default: Time
fcn_a          : ID of optional FUNCTION defining abscissa
                 default: not used
type_a         : Optional data type of abscissa
name_1         : Name of variable 1
fcn_1          : ID of FUNCTION defining variable 1
type_1         : Data type of variable 1
.              : 
name_n         : Name of variable n
fcn_n          : ID of FUNCTION defining variable n
type_n         : Data type of variable n

*OUTPUT_USER_COLLECTION
"Optional title"
coid,  outint,  outform
entype,  enid,  dptype,  fid,  extensive
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
filename       : File name for ASCII output (command ID and .out will be added as an extension)
coid           : Command ID
outint         : Output interval (see OUTPUT)
                 options:
                 0 -> Δt_imp
                 1 -> Δt_ascii
                 2 -> Δt_db
outform        : Output format
                 options:
                 0 -> .txt-files
                 1 -> .out-file
entype         : Entity type
                 options: N, NS, P, PS, G, ALL
enid           : Entity ID
dptype         : Data point type
                 options:
                 N -> nodes
                 E -> elements
fid            : Function ID
extensive      : Flag to output extensive (volume dependent) element properties
                 options:
                 0 -> intensive
                 1 -> extensive

*PARAMETER
%param = expression,  "description",  rid,  quantity
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
%param = expression: Parameter name and an expression defining its value
description    : Optional parameter description
rid            : Range ID for parameter manipulation in the GUI
quantity       : Physical quantity
                 options: mass, coordinate, length, displacement, area, volume,
		 time, stress, pressure, energy, power, acceleration, velocity, 
		 temperature, force, torque, moment, impulse, momentum, density, 
		 viscosity, srate, angledeg, anglerad, spindeg, spinrad, impint, 
		 cstiff, sstiff, tstiff, sdstiff, hcap, hcond
#example
    rho       = 7800, "density"
    nu        = 0.3,  "poisson's ratio"
#end

*PARAMETER_DEFAULT
%param=expression,  "description",  rid,  quantity
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
%param = expression: Parameter name and an expression defining its value
description    : Optional parameter description
rid            : Range ID for parameter manipulation in the GUI
quantity       : Physical quantity
                 options: mass, coordinate, length, displacement, area, volume, time, stress, pressure, energy, power, acceleration, velocity, temperature, force, torque, moment, impulse, momentum, density, viscosity, srate, angledeg, anglerad, spindeg, spinrad, impint, cstiff, sstiff, tstiff, sdstiff, hcap, hcond
#example
    %A = 640.0e6, "default yield stress", 0, stress
    %B = 450.0e6, "default hardening parameter", 0, stress
    %n = 0.3,     "default hardening exponent"
#end

*PARAMETER_RANGE_BOOL
rid
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
rid            : Range ID

*PARAMETER_RANGE_CONTINUOUS
rid
r_min,  r_max,  Δr
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
rid            : Range ID
r_min          : Minimum allowed parameter value
r_max          : Maximum allowed parameter value
Δr             : Parameter increment
                 default: Δr = (r_max-r_min)/100

*PARAMETER_RANGE_DISCRETE
rid
x_1,  "title_1"
.
x_n,  "title_n"
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
rid            : Range ID
x_1            : Value 1
title_1        : Description of value 1
.              : 
x_n            : Value n
title_n        : Description of value n

*PART
"Optional title"
pid,  mid,  -,  h,  α_max,  Δt^erode,  ε_geo^erode,  ε_v^erode
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
pid            : Unique part identification number or range of parts
mid            : Material identification number
-              : Reserved
h              : Shell thickness (only used for mass calculation, not in contact) or rebar diameter
                 default: 1
α_max          : External element face smoothing angle
                 default: no surface smoothing, i.e. ang_smooth = 0^circ
Δt^erode       : Time step size below which elements are eroded
                 default: 0
ε_geo^erode    : Effective deviatoric geometric strain above which elements are eroded
                 default: 1.0e20
ε_v^erode      : Volumetric strain above which elements are eroded
                 default: 1.0e20

*PARTICLE_AIR
"Optional title"
sbdid,  N_p^sid
type,  gid,  dsf,  -,  -,  -,  -,  t_end
ρ_0,  e_0,  γ,  v
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
sbdid          : Subdomain ID
N_p^sbdid      : Number of particles
                 default: not used
type           : Air type
                 options:
                 AIR -> air at 1atm and 293K
                 VOID -> vacuum
                 USER -> user defined
gid            : Geometry ID
dsf            : Particle density scale factor (particles per unit volume)
                 default: 1
-              : Reserved
-              : Reserved
-              : Reserved
-              : Reserved
t_end          : Particle deactivation time or FUNCTION (fcn)
                 options: time or fcn
                 default: not used
ρ_0            : Density (this line is only used if type=USER)
e_0            : Energy per unit volume
γ              : Fraction between C_p and C_v
v              : Co-volume at ρ = ρ_0

*PARTICLE_DETONATION
"Optional title"
dpid
x_d,  y_d,  z_d,  t_d,  R,  fast,  gid,  sid
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
dpid           : Detonation point ID
x_d, y_d, z_d  : Detonation point or function (fcn)
t_d            : Detonation time or function (fcn)
R              : Detonation radius
fast           : Flag to activate simplified (fast) detonation path calculation
                 options:
                 0 -> default detonation path
                 1 -> simplified detonation path
gid            : Detonation geometry ID
                 default: not used
sid            : Subdomain ID
                 default: not used

*PARTICLE_DOMAIN
entype,  enid,  N_p,  μ,  pfac,  c_dec,  xsmooth,  t_end
x_0,  y_0,  z_0,  x_1,  y_1,  z_1
bc_x0,  bc_y0,  bc_z0,  bc_x1,  bc_y1,  bc_z1
δ_0^max,  ctype,  SPH_uniform
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
entype         : Structure entity type for particle structure interaction
                 options: 0, P, PS, ALL
enid           : Structure entity ID
N_p            : Total number of particles
μ              : Particle-structure contact friction
                 default: 0.0
pfac           : Particle-structure contact stiffness
c_dec          : Impulse transfer smoothing time (gas-structure)
                 default: 0.0
xsmooth        : Spatial impulse smoothing level
                 default: inactive
t_end          : Particle deactivation time
                 default: 1.0e10
x_0            : Particle domain minimum x-coordinate
y_0            : Particle domain minimum y-coordinate
z_0            : Particle domain minimum z-coordinate
x_1            : Particle domain maximum x-coordinate
y_1            : Particle domain maximum y-coordinate
z_1            : Particle domain maximum z-coordinate
bc_x0          : Boundary condition at x=x_0
                 options:
                 0 -> free
                 1 -> rigid reflecting boundary
                 2 -> fully clamped (SPH only)
bc_y0          : Boundary condition at y=y_0
                 options:
                 0 -> free
                 1 -> rigid reflecting boundary
                 2 -> fully clamped (SPH only)
bc_z0          : Boundary condition at z=z_0
                 options:
                 0 -> free
                 1 -> rigid reflecting boundary
                 2 -> fully clamped (SPH only)
bc_x1          : Boundary condition at x=x_1
                 options:
                 0 -> free
                 1 -> rigid reflecting boundary
                 2 -> fully clamped (SPH only)
bc_y1          : Boundary condition at y=y_1
                 options:
                 0 -> free
                 1 -> rigid reflecting boundary
                 2 -> fully clamped (SPH only)
bc_z1          : Boundary condition at z=z_1
                 options:
                 0 -> free
                 1 -> rigid reflecting boundary
                 2 -> fully clamped (SPH only)
δ_0^max        : Max allowed initial contact penetration
                 default: 0
ctype          : Particle-structure contact type
                 options:
                 0 -> point to surface
                 1 -> sphere to surface
SPH_uniform    : Flag to swith from uniform SPH node mass to uniform SPH smoothing length
                 options:
                 0 -> uniform SPH node mass
                 1 -> uniform SPH smoothing length

*PARTICLE_DOMAIN_CLEANUP
"Optional title"
sid,  t_clean,  gid,  repeat,  m_min,  W_min,  v_min
n_x,  n_y,  n_z
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
sid            : Subdomain ID
t_clean        : Clean-up time
gid            : Geometry ID
repeat         : Flag to repeat clean-up at time interval t_clean
                 options:
                 0: clean up once
                 1: repeat
m_min          : Minimum SPH fragment mass
                 default: not used
W_min          : Minimum SPH fragment kinetic energy
                 default: not used
v_min          : Minimum SPH fragment velocity
                 default: not used
n_x, n_y, n_z  : SPH fragment velocity projection direction
                 default: not used

*PARTICLE_HE
"Optional title"
sbdid,  N_p^sbdid
type,  gid,  follow,  dsf,  -,  -,  -,  t_end
ρ_0,  e_0,  γ,  v,  D
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
sbdid          : Subdomain ID
N_p^sbdid      : Number of superposed particle layers
                 default: not active
type           : High explosive type
                 options:
                 preset: see list below
                 user: user defined
gid            : Geometry ID
follow         : Force particles to follow overlapping elements
                 options:
                 0: no
                 1: yes
dsf            : Particle density scale factor (particles per unit volume)
                 default: 1
-              : Reserved
-              : Reserved
-              : Reserved
t_end          : Particle deactivation time or FUNCTION (fcn)
                 options: time or fcn
                 default: not used
ρ_0            : Density (this line is only used if type=USER)
e_0            : Energy per unit volume
γ              : Fraction between C_p and C_v at zero co-volume (ideal gas regime)
v              : Co-volume at ρ = ρ_0
D              : Detonation velocity

*PARTICLE_SOIL
"Optional title"
sbdid,  N_p^sbdid
type,  gid,  dsf,  -,  -,  -,  -,  t_end
ρ_0,  k,  μ,  ξ,  v,  η
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
sbdid          : Subdomain ID
N_p^sbdid      : Number of particles
                 default: not used
type           : Soil type
                 options:
                 DRY: dry sand
                 WET: fully saturated wet sand
                 USER: user defined
gid            : Geometry ID
dsf            : Particle density scale factor (particles per unit volume)
                 default: 1
-              : Reserved
-              : Reserved
-              : Reserved
-              : Reserved
t_end          : Particle deactivation time or FUNCTION (fcn)
                 options: time or fcn
                 default: not used
ρ_0            : Density (this line is only used if type=USER)
k              : Grain contact stiffness
μ              : Grain contact coefficient of friction
ξ              : Grain contact damping coefficient
v              : Fill fraction (typically between 0.58 and 0.62)
η              : Dimensionless shear cap coefficient

*PARTICLE_SPH
"Optional title"
sbdid,  N_p^sbdid
mid,  gid,  correction,  s,  dsf,  E2S,  slide,  t_end
Δ
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
sbdid          : Subdomain ID
N_p^sbdid      : Number of particles
                 default: not used
mid            : Material ID
gid            : Geometry ID
correction     : Dynamic SPH node coordinate correction
                 options:
                 0 -> weak correction
                 1 -> strong correction
                 2 -> no correction
s              : Smoothing length scale factor
                 default: 2.5
dsf            : Particle density scale factor (particles per unit volume)
                 default: 1
E2S            : SPH particles are activated as elements are eroded (element to SPH mapping)
                 options:
                 0 -> no
                 1-> yes
slide          : Sliding contact flag
                 options:
                 0 -> full merge
                 1 -> sliding only
t_end          : Particle deactivation time or FUNCTION (fcn)
                 options: time or fcn
                 default: not used
Δ              : ID of optional coordinate system defining SPH node distribution directions

*PARTICLE_SPH_JET
sbdid
x_1,  y_1,  z_1,  x_2,  y_2,  z_2,  R,  ξ
v_min,  m_min,  no_ecc
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
sbdid          : Particle subdomain ID
x_1, y_1, z_1  : Cylinder face center coordinate 1
x_2, y_2, z_2  : Cylinder face center coordinate 2
R              : Cylinder radius
ξ              : Dimensionless jet correction parameter
                 default: 0.1
v_min          : Cut-off velocity in jet length calculation
                 default: 0
m_min          : Threshold fragment mass
                 default: 0
no_ecc         : Flag to deactivate eccentricity correction
                 options:
                 0 -> jet eccentricity correction is active
                 1 -> jet eccentricity correction is inactive

