                 Z+ -> Any positive integer used to set seed
                 Z- -> Any negative integer used to set seed

*REDISTRIBUTE_MESH_CARTESIAN
coid
entype,  enid,  dir,  c_1,  c_2
x_c,  y_c,  z_c
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
coid           : Command ID
entype         : Entity type
                 options: G, P
enid           : Entity ID
dir            : Direction of redistribution
                 options: X, Y, Z, XY, YZ, ZX, XYZ
c_1            : Parameter for polynomial redistribution
c_2            : Parameter for exponential redistribution
x_c            : x-coordinate with highest node densit
y_c            : y-coordinate with highest node density
z_c            : z-coordinate with highest node density

*REFINE
entype,  enid,  level,  gid,  thick,  d_min,  α_max,  deactivate
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
entype         : Entity type
                 options: P, PS
enid           : Entity identification number
level          : Level of refinement
gid            : ID of a GEOMETRY that defines a sub-space for refinement
                 default: all elements in the selected part/part set will be refined
thick          : Optional special refinement level in through thickness direction. The option only works for structures that are modeled with one element in thickness direction.
                 default: same as level
d_min          : Minimum element dimension for refinement
                 default: all elements are refined
α_max          : External element face smoothing angle
                 default: no surface smoothing
deactivate     : Deactivated refine directions
                 options: 0, X, Y, Z, XY, YZ, ZX, XYZ

*REMAP
"Optional title"
coid
pid_from,  pid_to,  velo,  stress,  state,  defgrad
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
coid           : Command ID
pid_from       : ID of part from which data will be mapped
pid_to         : ID of part to which data will be mapped
velo           : Velocity flag
                 options:
                 0 -> velocity field is not mapped
                 1 -> velocity field is mapped
stress         : Stress flag
                 options:
                 0 -> stress field is not mapped
                 1 -> stress field is mapped
state          : State variable flag
                 options:
                 0 -> state variables are not mapped
                 1 -> state variables are mapped
defgrad        : Deformation gradient flag
                 options:
                 0 -> deformation gradient is not mapped
                 1 -> deformation gradient is mapped

