fid_2          : FUNCTION defining radial displacement of outer surface
fid_3          : FUNCTION defining axial displacement (z)
fid_4          : FUNCTION defining tangential displacement (θ)

*TRIM
entype,  enid,  nid_seed,  t_trim,  x,  y,  z
x_1,  y_1,  z_1
.
x_n,  y_n,  z_n
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
entype         : Entity type
                 options: P, PS
enid           : Entity ID
nid_seed       : Seed node id, marking material to keep after trimming
t_trim         : t_trim
x              : X-component of trimline projection direction
y              : Y-component of trimline projection direction
z              : Z-component of trimline projection direction
x_1            : X-coordinate of trim line point 1
y_1            : Y-coordinate of trim line point 1
z_1            : Z-coordinate of trim line point 1
.              : 
x_n            : X-coordinate of trim line point n
y_n            : Y-coordinate of trim line point n
z_n            : Z-coordinate of trim line point n

*TRIM_HOLE
"Optional title"
coid
entype,  enid,  tabid,  D,  L,  ΔR
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
coid           : Command ID
entype         : Entity type
                 options: P, PS
enid           : Entity ID
tabid          : Table ID
D              : Hole diameter
L              : Hole length
ΔR             : Radial trim padding
                 default: 0

*UNIT_SYSTEM
units,  temperature
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
units          : Unit system
                 options:
                 SI -> [m, kg, s]
                 MMTONS or MM/TON/S -> [mm, ton, s]
                 CMGUS or CM/G/US -> [cm, g, μs]
                 IPS -> [in, slinch, s]
                 MMKGMS or MM/KG/MS -> [mm, kg, ms]
                 CMGS or CM/G/S -> [cm, g, s]
                 MMGMS or MM/G/MS -> [mm, g, ms]
                 MMMGMS or MM/MG/MS -> [mm, mg, ms]
temperature    : Temperature units
                 options: K, C, F
                 default: K (F if units=IPS)

*VAA
"Optional title"
coid
entype_a,  enid_a,  entype_v,  enid_v,  tabid_m,  δ_ref,  Δ_hit
ψ_0,  ψ_1,  N_ψ,  θ_0,  θ_1,  N_θ
tid_f
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
coid           : Command ID
entype_a       : Armour entity type
                 options: P, PS, ALL
enid_a         : Armour entity identification number
entype_v       : Protected volume entity type
                 options: P, PS, AL
enid_v         : Protected volume entity identification number
tabid_m        : ID of table with material properties
δ_ref          : Critical reference material thickness at normal impact
Δ_hit          : Hit spot grid size
                 default: Δ_hit = 0.5 * δ_ref
psi_0          : Horizontal (azimuth) start angle
psi_1          : Horizontal (azimuth) end angle
N_psi          : Number of horizontal frames
θ_0            : Vertical start angle
θ_1            : Vertical end angle
N_θ            : Number of vertical frames
tid_f          : ID of table with edge effect properties by face set

*VELOCITY_CAP
v_max^N,  v_max^DP1,  v_max^DP2,  v_max^CFD
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
v_max^N        : Finite Element node velocity cap
                 default: no upper limit
v_max^DP1      : Discrete particle (SOIL and SPH) velocity cap
                 default: no upper limit
v_max^DP2      : Discrete particle (AIR and HE) velocity cap
                 default: no upper limit
v_max^CFD      : CFD velocity cap
                 default: no upper limit

*WELD
nsid,  stype,  pid,  nseg,  a,  roff
----------------------------------------------------------------
Variable         Description
nsid           : ID of node set defining weld path
stype          : Weld cross section discretization
                 options:
                 1 -> 1 triangle
                 2 -> 3 quads
                 3 -> 1 quad
pid            : Part ID of generated weld mesh
nseg           : Number of elements along weld path
                 default: Same discretization as the weld path
a              : Weld thickness (a-value)
roff           : Weld root offset

~convert_from_ 
~end_convert

~if
~else_if
~else
~end_if

~repeat iterations
~end_repeat
